# Brainiac reverse proxy (SYSTEM.md §16, ADR 0001).
# Fronts the app's HTTP surface (WebUI + REST) with TLS + a coarse network gate.
# The MCP server is stdio-only and is never network-exposed.
#
# Configure via environment (see .env.example):
#   SITE_ADDRESS     your domain (auto-HTTPS, recommended) · ":443" (add `tls internal`)
#                    Use ":80" for LOCAL DEV ONLY — off-box it sends bearer tokens
#                    and basic-auth in cleartext (#271). Require TLS in production.
#   BASIC_AUTH_USER  username
#   BASIC_AUTH_HASH  bcrypt hash — generate with: caddy hash-password --plaintext '…'
#
# ⚠️ basic_auth here is a COARSE network gate (keeps the open Layer-1 read surface
# off the public internet), NOT the multi-tenant boundary. The per-team boundary is
# Layer-2 principals (`principals:` in config, per-token namespace isolation, #120) —
# a single shared basic-auth credential cannot separate tenants. For multi-team
# sensitive data, configure principals and treat basic_auth as defense-in-depth.

{$SITE_ADDRESS} {
	# HSTS: once a browser has seen HTTPS, never downgrade to cleartext (#271).
	# Harmless on a domain/:443; a no-op for plain-HTTP :80 dev.
	header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains"

	basic_auth {
		{$BASIC_AUTH_USER} {$BASIC_AUTH_HASH}
	}
	reverse_proxy app:8080
}
